# Workflow Patterns

## Development Workflow
1. Plan before implementing ‚Äî use `/plan-feature` or `@planner`
2. Validate architecture ‚Äî use `@architect` before coding
3. Implement with tests ‚Äî follow TDD Red‚ÜíGreen‚ÜíRefactor
4. Review before merging ‚Äî use `/review` for multi-perspective feedback
5. Document changes ‚Äî update CHANGELOG, docstrings, ADRs

## Git Strategy
- Feature branches from `main`
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`
- Squash merge to main
{%- if with_gsd %}
- GSD-2 uses worktree isolation (branch-per-milestone)
{%- endif %}

## Task Runner Commands
```bash
task dev              # Start development servers
task test             # Run all tests
task test:unit        # Unit tests only
task lint             # All linters
task format           # Auto-format all code
task registry:generate # Regenerate constants from registry
task db:migrate       # Run Alembic migrations
```

## Registry Workflow
1. Edit `registry/naming_registry.json`
2. Run `task registry:validate`
3. Run `task registry:generate`
4. Commit both the registry and generated files
